Package ch.nolix.element.core

Class Time

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.nolix.element.core.Element
      • ch.nolix.element.core.Time
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Typed, TypeRequestable, Specified, IElement

    public final class Time
extends Element
    A time stores a point in time with a precision of 1 millisecond. A time stores a point in time according to the Gregorian calendar. Since the Gregorian calendar is not proleptic a time can only store a point in time after 1600-01-01 00:00:000. Not proleptic means that the Greogioan calender does officially not allow calculations backwards behind the point of its release, that was in 1582. A time is not mutable. Technically, a time is a wrapper around JDK's GregorianCalendar.
    Author:
    Silvan Wyss
